#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/types-and-traits.md:1
msgid "Types and Traits"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/types-and-traits.md:3
msgid "Use types to enforce invariants (`rust-type-invariants`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/types-and-traits.md:5
msgid "Leverage the type system to make illegal states _unrepresentable_."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/types-and-traits.md:8
msgid "Define newtypes to encode domain constraints."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/types-and-traits.md:11
msgid "// Good — a `Nice` value is guaranteed to be valid\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/types-and-traits.md:14
msgid "// Bad — `i8` admits invalid values for nice levels\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/types-and-traits.md:19
msgid "Prefer enums over bare integers and boolean flags."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/types-and-traits.md:22
msgid "// Good — access mode is constrained by the enum\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/types-and-traits.md:29
msgid "// Bad — `u8` admits invalid values\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/types-and-traits.md:34
msgid "Encode invariants in generic parameters where needed."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/types-and-traits.md:38
msgid "// Good — only unsafe code can write to sensitive MMIO\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/types-and-traits.md:39
#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/types-and-traits.md:44
msgid "/* .. */"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/types-and-traits.md:43
msgid "// Good — safe code can write to insensitive MMIO\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/types-and-traits.md:51
msgid ""
"Asterinas uses this pattern widely, for example with newtypes such as "
"`CpuId` and `AlignedUsize<const N: u16>`."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/types-and-traits.md:55
msgid ""
"See also: PR [\\#2265](https://github.com/asterinas/asterinas/"
"pull/2265#discussion_r2266214191) and [\\#2514](https://github.com/asterinas/"
"asterinas/pull/2514)."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/types-and-traits.md:59
msgid "Prefer enum over trait objects for closed sets (`enum-over-dyn`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/types-and-traits.md:61
msgid ""
"When the set of variants is known and closed, an enum is often preferable to "
"`Box<dyn Trait>` for both performance and pattern-matching expressiveness."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/types-and-traits.md:66
msgid "// Good — closed set modeled as an enum\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/types-and-traits.md:74
msgid "Encapsulate fields behind getters (`getter-encapsulation`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/types-and-traits.md:76
msgid ""
"Do not make fields public when a simple getter method would do. A getter "
"preserves naming flexibility and leaves room for future invariants."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/types-and-traits.md:82
msgid "// Good — field is private, accessed via getter\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/types-and-traits.md:92
msgid "// Bad — public field exposes representation\n"
msgstr ""
